The initial development of this software was carried out as part of
the SINBAD project (http://slim.eos.ubc.ca) with financial support, secured through ITF,
from the following organizations: BG, BP, Chevron, ExxonMobil, and Shell.
SINBAD is part of the collaborative research & development (CRD) grant number 334810-05
funded by the Natural Science and Engineering Research Council (NSERC).
